>Description:
Running Check Syntax on a saved program makes Spidey think that
the program has changed (and thus gives the "file ... is not saved"
warning).

>How-To-Repeat:
Start drscheme.
Enter a 1-line program, (define f 12).
Save the program.
Run Check Syntax.
Start Spidey.

